Tiller Idrettslag is a Norwegian sports club from Trondheim, Sr-Trndelag. It has sections for association football, team handball, ice hockey, Nordic skiing and biathlon. It was established on 15 January 1916.[2] The men's football team plays in the Third Division, the fourth tier of Norwegian football, after being relegated from Fair Play ligaen in 2011 The men's football team have generally played in the Third Division since 1997, with the exception of 2000 and 2011 when they played in the Second Division. In 2008 Tiller won their Third Division group and contested a playoff to win promotion to the Second Division again, but lost to Nardo FK. Tiller also won their Third Division group in 2010 and won 64 on aggregate against IL Stjrdals-Blink in the playoff and won promotion. Note: Flags indicate national team as has been defined under FIFA eligibility rules. Players may hold more than one non-FIFA nationality.
